				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=39462&amp;sid=0a84f8faffa71126368c85e0ec8c6cda"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, folks. I had a bit of anxiety before attempting this fight, but was pleasantly surprised that I was able to (read: easily) solo this at 50. This mini guide starts you in the Vah Shir outpost in Grimling Forest. Oh, and by the way, gear isn't really a big factor here. As long as your gear is OK for a 50th level character, you should do fine. Why is that? Well, because you are barely going to do any fighting. Here's the details on what occurred:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Preparations</span>
<br />

<br />
First thing to do is scout out the area and get familiar with where everyone/thing is. It isn't a complicated part as there are really only three important things to know. First, buy your acrylia sphere. The vendor is towards the back, left side of the outpost. She sells 3 different spheres. You want the cheapest one (61pp and some change for me). Next, find Scout Husman. He is near the entrance of the outpost, guarding the first building. Finally, get to the grimling camp where the war takes place. I outline that next...
<br />

<br />
Summon your warder, buff with vermin, quickening, spiritual brawn, spirit of monkey (more buffs if you like, but I found no need). Buff yourself with SOW (in case things go bad) and Spiritual Light. Keep in mind if things go bad you can run to the zone or back to the outpost. They are both very close. Make a hotkey "/assist scout husman". Be aware some of the mobs do cast instill, which overwrites SOW. I can't imagine you needing to worry about it tho. I resisted everything except screaming terror 2x. My resists are very average.
<br />

<br />
Now, move your warder down to the grimling camp. To get to the camp, walk straight out of the outpost to the little bridge. Cross the bridge, and crest the next hill. Walk down the backside of the hill. The camp has 2 little tents in a valley over that hill. When you get there, there will be 5 or 6 grimlings spawned there. Send your warder in to kill them all. You will have to move down to between the tents to target them all, as there are a few casters inside the tents. Your warder will tear them a new one, so just med up while your pet does the work for you. After the camp is clear, park your pet in the middle of the camp, med to full, and head back to the outpost.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Get this party started</span>
<br />

<br />
The quest is started by turning your acrylia sphere into Scout Husman. He will say something about a good day for a raid. Just follow the dialog until he starts walking out from the outpost. He will head (slowly) towards the grimling camp where fluffy is waiting. Once he is up on the hill, he will pause and then sprint down to the middle of the camp and become rooted right in the middle. Immediately, 5 or so grimling will spawn from around the camp, and make a b-line for the center where the scout now is. DONT PANIC! They are all green to you. During the war, I actually went UP in mana. You should keep your healing spell up just in case you need it. Remember, let your warder do the work. You just set him up. As the grimlings attack, stand next to the scout, and target each grimling that comes in. Hit them once or twice, then /pet attack. If your pet is busy with another grimling (which he will make short work of), it will queue up the attack (meaning, once he is done with the mob he is on, he will go to that mob next). The important thing to remember here is that the scout must not die. I had no problems keeping him alive, just make sure you are paying attention. If he is being hit then find the mob hitting him, and get them to aggro you. They should aggro very easily back to you.
<br />

<br />
After the first wave, sit and med. The scout will regen quickly from whatever damage he may have taken. My scout was never below 90% during the fight. There is about a 2-3 minute pause between waves. Don't let your guard down! Keep an eye out around the camp for more grimlings to spawn. If you see them, target and send the pet in immediately. My pet usually killed the first spawn before it even got close to the camp. Then, as  he was fighting that one, I'd go around tagging all the other ones that spawned. Another thing to watch for is if you see the scout say, "Time to die, so-and-so" then use your "/assist scout husman" key.  That message most likely means a caster has started casting on your scout. You want to get the aggro off of him as soon as you can.
<br />

<br />
I had about 8 waves before the officer spawned. He was a bit tougher than the rest, but still green at 50. Once you kill the officer, loot all he has, and hand the scalp into the scout. He will give you the copper medal of war. One note: I had another wave spawn on me after I killed the officer. Don't panic. Make sure you loot your scalp, then kill the wave. Make sure you keep the scout alive. As soon as that wave is done, hand the scout the scalp for your medal. I've heard if the scout dies at this point, you can just buy another sphere, repeat this process, and after a few waves he will accept your scalp. I didn't personally need this, so I can't vouche for it. Also, once you have the medal, b-line it out of there. No need to continue as you have all you needed.
<br />

<br />
That is about it. Was an easy fight. Took about 45 minutes total to do solo. Just remember not to panic, and don't lose your head. AND DONT ACCIDENTLY TARGET HUSMAN DURING YOUR FIGHTS!! If you pay attention and stay calm, you will succeed.
<br />

<br />
I hope this helps some of you on your journey to get your claws!
<br />

<br />
Aowin Ringbearer
<br />
50th Vah Shir Beastlord
<br />
Proud member of the Valiant Crusaders
<br />
Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
